Interface SequenceGapInformation.Provider

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultAminoAcidSequence, DefaultNucleotideGraphSequence, DefaultNucleotideSequence, DefaultSequenceDocument, OligoSequenceDocument
    Enclosing class:
    SequenceGapInformation

    public static interface SequenceGapInformation.Provider
    An interface that SequenceDocuments can optionally to implement to indicate they may provide a (potentially) pre-built SequenceGapInformation
    Since:
    API 4.60 (Geneious 5.6.0)

      Methods

      SequenceGapInformation getSequenceGapInformation(boolean createIfNecessary)

    • Method Detail

      • getSequenceGapInformation

        SequenceGapInformation getSequenceGapInformation(boolean createIfNecessary)
        Returns a SequenceGapInformation associated with this sequence.
        Parameters:
        createIfNecessary - true to create a SequenceGapInformation even if the sequence doesn't already have one cached. The implementation may choose to cache the result it returns.
        Returns:
        a SequenceGapInformation associated with this sequence or potentially null if createIfNecessary is false
        Since:
        API 4.60 (Geneious 5.6.0)
